I have been working on a class of shift-register PRN's [mod 2] whose
characteristic polynomial has the form
	x^(2^n) + x^(2^n -1) + x^(2^(n-1)-1) + x^(2^(n-2)-1)+...+x^7+x^3+x+1
where n>1 . I have determined the period of these generators for n=2 to 7 .
For example, the degree 128 polynomial gives a generator with a period > 2^96 .

   I have no results on figures of merit for these generators. I believe that
with n=20 (degree > 1000000) and an algorithmically incompressible seed (a 
concept due to G.J. Chaitin ) , one can obtain very good generators. For more
information on the application of algorithmic information theory to these
generators with high degree characteristic polynomial, or for my results
on the generators above with polynomial degrees 4 , 8, ... 128 , please send me
an email message at	dbernier@mat.ulaval.ca     .

				David Bernier
